@5004 = ~Bloodthirst +3~
@5005 = ~Before the Lord of Murder laid his claim to his title, for a time he was naught but a petty killer. When Bhaal first drew blood in a Baldurian back-alley, it leaked into the cobblestone pavement and lingered, uncleaned and unnoticed by the otherwise uncaring denizens of Baldur's Gate. When Bhaal ascended to godhood, that dried blood warped and formed a jagged blade, as if a promise made in that alley had been fulfilled by Bhaal's ascent. Members of Bhaal's clergy—outright forbidden in most parts, but ever-present in the shadows—found the blade and beheld it as a holy relic until their lord's death, where it was lost in the chaos that proceeded. Only those of dark hearts may wield this blade.

